Chocoalte Buckwheat Waffles - gf
  --Bon Appetit

Toppings:
1/4 c mixed buckwheat groats, black and/or white sesame seeds, and/or flaxseeds
2 tsp + 2 tbsp maple syrup
pinch kosher salt
1 c whole milk ricotta

Preheat oven to 300F. Toss buckwheat, seeds, 2 tsp maple syrup, and salt until evenly coated; spread out onto a rimmed baking sheet. Bake until dry to the touch and toasty smelling, 12-15 min. Stir to recoat and transfer to a sheet of parchment paper. Let cool. Whisk ricotta and remaining 2 tbsp syrup in a small bowl until smooth. Set aside.

Waffles:
1 c buckwheat flour
1/2 c dutch process unsweetened cocoa powder
1/4 c flaxseed meal
1 1/4 tsp kosher salt
1 tsp baking powder
1 tsp baking soda
2 large eggs, room temp
2 c buttermilk
1/2 c virgin coconut oil, melted
1/4 c packed dark brown sugar
2 tsp vanilla
2 oz bittersweet chocolate, coarsley chopped

Heat waffle iron on medium. Whisk flour, cocoa, flaxseed meal, salt, baking powder, and baking soda in a large bowl to combine. Whisk eggs, buttermilk, coconut oil, sugar, and vanilla in a medium bowl until smooth. Add wet to dry and whisk until smooth; mix in chocolate. Lightly coat iron with nonstick spray. Scoop batter onto iron (it should cover the entire surface; amount varies per model) and cook waffles until you smell a blast of chocolaty aroma and edges are slightly darkened, ~3 min per batch. Remove carefully, waffles will be extra tender.

Serve waffles with whipped topping, crumble, and maple syrup.


Notes: can sub alt-milk + 2 tbsp white vinegar for buttermilk
